Juneteenth is a day of reflection and renewal. It is a pride-filled day taken to appreciate the African American experience and is inclusive of all races, ethnicities, and nationalities in allyship.
Join us as we reflect on our past and acknowledge the work we still have to do. @meditatewitheve and @wizdomisms lead us in an exercise focused on increasing our ability to listen with our full attention, bringing more mindfulness and kindness to our allyship.

node.title: Mindful Allyship with Eve & Dr. Wizdom Powell

Back to school is a season fraught with emotional challenges for kids, parents, and teachers alike — excitement and anxiety about what the year holds, sadness about summer ending, and for many, issues with self-esteem, time management, and for parents, letting go! ⁠

Enter our Back to School collection, a syllabus for parents, teachers, and students filled with meditations and mindfulness exercises, all selected to help you start the school year off right. 📚

node.text: Reflect for a moment on a past challenge. Can you express gratitude for this experience? Has it shaped who you are today, made you stronger, or more resilient? Taking this perspective can help us see today’s difficulties as exciting, like puzzles waiting to be solved, opportunities to be seized.
